stories.text: I am starting to notice that social media is having a negative effect on me.  I get value from places like Hacker News and others.  There are some good information on the internet.  The problem is that I seem to be addict to it and I need to stop.  How do you control your urge from checking social media websites often?   Do I have to leave my phone at home?
stories.title: Ask HN: How to stop my addiction to social media?

stories.text:
I remember last year there was a lot of buzz and discussions around Github Copilot and it's impact on day to day life of software engineers. Recently noticed that Github Copilot is out of pilot and would be charging money for it soon. With this I was wondering :

* Is someone actually using Github Copilot for day to day work?

* How often do you use it to write parts of the production code?

* What are the use cases for it?

* Is it worth it?
stories.title: Ask HN: Do you use GitHub Copilot?
